<section>
	<h2 class="page-header mrgn-tp-sm" id="intro">Introduction</h2>
	<p>Grids create boxes of content, which is typically the desired result.  However, there are times when content needs to reflow around the grids.  The <code>mrgn-*-md</code> creates margin of 15px and it mimics the same gutter on a grid. This is important to understand when mixing grids and non-grids in the same row.  In order for the content will reflow around the grid cell, yet have the gutters match, you must apply both the <code>mrgn-lft-md</code> and <code>mrgn-rght-md</code> to the non-grid content.</p>
</section>

